passages.text:
You wake up in a strange room, surrounding by cats. Everything inside this room looks so familiar: the chair, the lamp, the laptop, and the photos on the wall. It looks like your bedroom, but you can tell that it is not. 
[[Where am I?]]
passages.name: Introduce

passages.text:
You have no clue. You just survived another day as usual and suddenly, boom, you are here. 
You look at the cats, trying to figure out who they are.
A Siamese cat, a Ragdoll cat, and a Maine Coon cat.
Awww, they are just three cutie pies and what else can they be?
ALIENS?!
You are totally lost.
[[Where is my phone?]]
passages.name: Where am I?

passages.text:
You decide to check your phone to see what's going on. You open one of your pockets but nothing is there, and you try another one, same result.
Wait, Wait a mintue...
WHERE IS MY PHONE?!
You look around.
There is a phone on the table.
You pick it up and unlock it with your passcode.
[[This is not my phone]]
passages.name: Where is my phone?

passages.text:
Eventhough the passcode is the same, the applications, the wallpaper, and the notes are so familiar to you.
But just like this room, you can feel it that this is not your room. 
And this is not your phone.
What is happening here?
passages.name: This is not my phone
